        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued August 2 at 11:30PM CDT until August 3 at 12:30AM CDT by NWS Amarillo TX</headline>
        <description>SVRAMA

The National Weather Service in Amarillo has issued a

* Severe Thunderstorm Warning for...
Northern Cimarron County in the Panhandle of Oklahoma...

* Until 1230 AM CDT.

* At 1130 PM CDT, a severe thunderstorm was located 4 miles northeast
of Kenton, or 25 miles northwest of Boise City, moving east at 15
mph.

HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and quarter size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor damage to roofs, siding, and trees is possible.
Hail damage to vehicles is expected.

* Locations impacted include...
Black Mesa Park and Kenton.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.

Torrential rainfall is occurring with this storm, and may lead to
flash flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded roadways.</instruction>
